title: Kinahan: The True Story of Ireland's Mafia
overview: Kinahan: The True Story of Ireland's Mafia tracks the Kinahan Cartel from its beginnings as a small-time street dealing operation in 1980s Dublin, to one the world's most feared and notorious criminal organisations. It is a story of gangland feuding, double dealing, betrayal, international law enforcement, and murder.Providing new insight, information and exclusive interviews, this four-part series tells the in-depth story of the cartel known as the Kinahan Transnational Criminal Organisation (KTCO), with roots that start in Ireland but spread to the UK, mainland Europe and around the world.
